  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Assigned counts enable managers to delegate inventory count tasks to specific staff members, allowing for a focused audit of different divisions within your store's inventory. Managers can easily assign these counts, set due dates, and manage conflicts with ongoing counts. This method is well-suited for routine inventory management, such as monthly counts. After the counts are completed and submitted by staff, an Inventory Manager or higher can review the results, reconcile any discrepancies, and make necessary adjustments before finalizing the inventory.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Streamlined Delegation</strong> - Easily assign inventory count tasks to staff, ensuring specific inventory areas are accurately covered.</p></li><li><p><strong>Time Management</strong> - Set due dates for count assignments, ensuring timely completion and keeping inventory management on schedule.</p></li><li><p><strong>Conflict Resolution</strong>: Manage and resolve any overlapping or conflicting counts, maintaining a smooth and organized process.</p></li></ul><h3 id=\"InventoryCounts:AssigningCounts-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932427464/Inventory+Count+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932427464\" data-linked-resource-version=\"7\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Inventory Count Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932591186/Inventory+Counts+Cycle+Counts+Unassigned+Counts\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932591186\" data-linked-resource-version=\"14\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Inventory Counts: Cycle Counts / Unassigned Counts</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1930494567/Inventory+Counts+Performing+an+Assigned+Count\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1930494567\" data-linked-resource-version=\"10\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Inventory Counts: Performing an Assigned Count</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932591200/Inventory+Counts+Pausing+Reassigning+and+Deleting+Counts\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932591200\" data-linked-resource-version=\"12\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Inventory Counts: Pausing, Reassigning, and Deleting Counts</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1932558411\" rel=\"nofollow\">Inventory Counts: Reconciling Counts</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932624055/Inventory+Status+Overview\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932624055\" data-linked-resource-version=\"7\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Inventory Status Overview</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932296330/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"InventoryCounts:AssigningCounts-AssigningCountstoaStaffMember\">Assigning Counts to a Staff Member</h2><p>On the RepairQ Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Inventory</strong> \u2192 <strong>Inventory Summary</strong>. On the Inventory Summary screen use the filters to create a list of items for an assignment. We recommend assigning counts based on scoped inventory results, to make the count more manageable for the assignees. You can filter results based on item types, manufacturer, serialized items, etc.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: Assigned counts will appear on the assignee's <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933705356/Getting+Started+The+RepairQ+Dashboard\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933705356\" data-linked-resource-version=\"9\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Dashboard</a> as a reminder.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932296330/Assign%201.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932296330/Assign%205.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"InventoryCounts:AssigningCounts-AssignAllFilteredItems\">Assign All Filtered Items</h3><p>To assign the count for\u00a0<strong>all</strong> filtered results (including multiple pages of results) <strong>click the Options button (\u22ee)\u00a0</strong> on the right side of the page to expand available options. From the list of options, <strong>click Assign All Counts</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932296330/Assign%206.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"204\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932296330/Assign%207.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"InventoryCounts:AssigningCounts-AssignSpecificInventoryItems\">Assign Specific Inventory Items</h3><p>After filtering your results, <strong>click the selection boxes</strong> to the left of the item(s) you want to assign. Then <strong>click the Options (\u22ee) button</strong> to expand the available options. From the list of selections, click<strong> Assign Counts</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932296330/Assign%208.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"204\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932296330/Assign%209.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>On the Assign Count pop-up, fill out the fields to assign the count to the corresponding staff member. Once you have made your selections, <strong>click Assign Counts</strong>.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Location</strong>- Select the store location where the count will be performed.</p></li><li><p><strong>Manager</strong>- The assigned manager who will reconcile the counts when completed.</p></li><li><p><strong>Assignee</strong>- Select the staff member the count will be assigned to.</p></li><li><p><strong>Due Date</strong>- Set the date and time the count needs to be completed by.</p></li><li><p><strong>Conflicts</strong>- Select the appropriate conflict resolution for multiple assignees counting the same items:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Re-assign any pending counts to this staff member</strong> - If any of these items are already assigned to another staff member, they will be reassigned to the current staff member selected.</p></li><li><p><strong>Skip items already assigned to another staff member</strong> - If any of these items are already assigned to another staff member, it will leave them assigned to the original person and skip an assignment. This will help reduce duplicate item counts being assigned to multiple people.</p></li><li><p><strong>Allow both staff members to count the same item</strong> - New counts will be created and assigned to the new staff member while keeping any previous count assignment for this item. This may cause you to have duplicate item assignments in your Inventory Count Summary. We recommend this option only if you plan to compare <strong>Counted</strong> totals between staff members and delete the count that is inaccurate.</p></li></ul></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932296330/Assign%2010.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>After assigning the count, the Inventory Count List will show all items ready to be counted (Counting status), due dates, and assignees.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932296330/Assign%2011.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.21.X</p>",
